    "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- Add a startup warning when `-bind` is specified without a dedicated onion socket (`-bind=<addr>=onion`) but `-listenonion` is enabled\r\n- Without a dedicated onion bind, incoming Tor connections arrive on the regular bind address and cannot be distinguished from IPv4 connections, causing `-netinfo` to misreport them\r\n- The warning informs users to add `-bind=127.0.0.1:8334=onion` for accurate connection tracking\r\n\r\nfixes #33458\r\n\r\n## Test plan\r\n\r\n- [x] `cmake --build build --target bitcoind` compiles cleanly\r\n- [x] `./build/bin/test_bitcoin --run_test=net_tests` passes (16 test cases)\r\n",
